RED FLAG 7 — Unit conversion errors (ppb vs ppm)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Bug: Vendor CoAs report in different units:
   Peter Greven: ppb (parts per billion)
   Vertellus: ppb (mixed with some ppm)
   Most others: ppm or µg/g

Extractor sometimes treats ppb as ppm (1000× overstatement) or treats 
ppm as ppb (1000× understatement).

Fix in annexure_converter.py:

1. Explicitly detect unit column headers in each CoA table:
   Recognizable unit strings: "ppm", "ppb", "µg/g", "mg/kg", "µg/kg", 
   "mg/g", "%"

2. Normalize all extracted values to µg/g (= ppm):
   ppb → ppm: divide by 1000
   mg/kg → ppm: 1:1 (identical)
   µg/kg → ppm: divide by 1000
   mg/g → ppm: multiply by 1000
   % → ppm: multiply by 10000

3. Store both the raw value and the normalized value + source unit in 
   the annexure record. Flag in audit trail.

4. For each element extracted, sanity-check: value should be < 10000 ppm 
   for any excipient element concentration. If value > 10000, log warning 
   ("possible unit interpretation error").

Acceptance:
Peter Greven V = 2030 ppb → 2.030 µg/g in AI report
Vertellus As = <20 ppb → 0.020 µg/g in AI report  
BASF Cd = <0.05 mg/kg → 0.05 µg/g in AI report

