RED FLAG 14 — Handling of "Not analyzed" and "NA" cells
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Bug: Some vendor CoAs use "Not analyzed" or "NA" for elements not tested. 
Extractor sometimes treats these as 0.0 (understatement) or as PDE 
placeholder (overstatement).

Fix in annexure_converter.py:

1. Recognize "not analyzed", "not tested", "not applicable", "n/a", "NA", 
   "—", "-", empty cell.

2. When encountered, DO NOT default to zero.
   Options depending on annexure context:
   
   IF vendor declares "no ICH Q3D elements intentionally added":
       Use ICH Q3D Option 1 Oral PDE × 0.3 (30% threshold) as worst case
       Evidence type: "declared_not_added"
   
   IF vendor states "elements below reporting limit for this method":
       Use method LOD/LOQ if extractable
       Evidence type: "below_LOD"
   
   IF neither declaration nor LOD available:
       Use 0.05 (typical LOQ for ICP-MS) as conservative default
       Evidence type: "conservative_default"
       Flag for manual review in log

3. Never leave cells as raw 0.0 unless the vendor explicitly states 
   "Not detected" AND provides LOQ = 0.0 (impossible).

Acceptance:
No element concentration in Table 4/5/6/7 is bare 0.0 without justification 
(either from vendor declaration + LOD interpretation, or worst-case default).

